pesticide.PPE: long-sleeved shirt and long pants; waterproof gloves; shoes plus socks; protective eyewear; NIOSH-approved particulate filtering facepiece respirator with any N, R or P filter or NIOSH-approved elastomeric particulate respirator with any N, R, or P filter or NIOSH-approved powered air purifying respirator with an HE filter

Active_Ingredients.name: Heat-killed Burkholderia rinojensis strain A396 cells and spent fermentation media

Safety_Information.general_Info: Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15–20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
